{"lemma":"حَلالٌ","slug":"حَلالٌ","root":"ح.ل.ل","root_slug":"ح-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَلال","root":"حلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8751","n8752","n8754"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"allowed, permitted, allowable, admissible, permissible."},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"allowed, permitted, allowable, admissible, permissible.; halal, that which is permitted by God."},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lawful, legal, licit, legitimate."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَّ (ḥalla, “to be permitted”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lawful possession"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare حَلَّ (ḥalla, “to be allowed, to be lawful”), Classical Syriac ܚܠܠ (ḥallel, “to cleanse, to purify”)."},"ipa":["/ħa.laːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8751","headword_ar":"حَلَالٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lawful, allowable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaraAmN","text_ar":"حَرَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAlN","text_ar":"حِلَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliylN","text_ar":"حَلِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) a metaphorical signification, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~u AlEuqodapi","text_ar":"حَلُّ العُقْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ the untying of the knot ”] : according to some, meaning what is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not forbidden;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"including what is disapproved and what is not disapproved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to others, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which one is not punishable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN HalaAlK","text_ar":"مَالٌ حَلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth lawfully acquired."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu HalaAlK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ حَلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A legitimate son:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ingenuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest, person."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHulowu AlHalaAlu","text_ar":"الحُلْوُ الحَلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Language in which is nothing that induces doubt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man in whom is nothing that induces doubt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlw","text_ar":"حلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hil~N","text_ar":"هُوَ حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is lawful, allowable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free, to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bil~N","text_ar":"بِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hil~N","text_ar":"هُوَ حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning the same; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w~bil~N","text_ar":"وّبِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiya","text_ar":"هِيَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabil~N","text_ar":"وَبِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"li$aAribK Hil~N","text_ar":"لِشَارِبٍ حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bl","text_ar":"بل"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has quitted his state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHil~N","text_ar":"مُحِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlA_iHoraAmi","text_ar":"مِنَ الاـِحْرَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~N","text_ar":"حِلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) or this last signifies one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has not become in that state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) by rule one should say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAl~N","text_ar":"حَالٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is not used in this sense. (K.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from any obstacle to marriage, as, for instance, by having accomplished the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~ap","text_ar":"عِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b4-  See also 5."}],"source_refs":["K","S","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n8752","headword_ar":"حِلَالٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaAlN","text_ar":"حَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n8754","headword_ar":"حَلَّالٌ","root":"Hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who solves astronomical problems."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AD%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84/","headword_ar":"حلال","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_15","lexicon_en":"Ibn Mālik, al-Alfāẓ al-Mukhtalifa fī l-Maʿānī al-Muʾtalifa (d. 1274 CE)","lexicon_ar":"الألفاظ المختلفة في المعاني المؤتلفة لابن مالك","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22454#84d796","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">بَاب الْحَلَال</span><br><br><span>مُبَاح مرخص مُطلق طلق</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22454#60cd34","body_html":"<span>الحلال: كل شيء لا يعاقَب عليه باستعماله.<br></span><br>الحلال: ما أطلق الشرع فعله، مأخوذ من: الحل، وهو الفتح."}]}}